Changes:
```typescript
const MAX_OUTPUT_BYTES = 1024 * 1024; // 1 MB
let stdoutBytes = 0;
let stderrBytes = 0;
const stdoutChunks: Buffer[] = [];
const stderrChunks: Buffer[] = [];

child.stdout.on('data', (chunk: Buffer) => {
  stdoutBytes += chunk.length;
  if (stdoutBytes > MAX_OUTPUT_BYTES) {
    child.kill();
    reject(new Error(`npm view stdout exceeded 1 MB for ${packageName}`));
    return;
  }
  stdoutChunks.push(chunk);
});
child.stderr.on('data', (chunk: Buffer) => {
  stderrBytes += chunk.length;
  if (stderrBytes > MAX_OUTPUT_BYTES) {
    child.kill();
    // stderr overflow is non-fatal — just stop accumulating
    return;
  }
  stderrChunks.push(chunk);
});
```

Constraints:
- The `reject` call inside the data handler will fire after the Promise was already constructed. Guard against double-rejection by checking if the timer is still active or using a `settled` flag
- The `MAX_OUTPUT_BYTES` constant should be defined at the top of the function or module
